criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Burn patients admitted to Motahary burn center with documented inhalation injury (as
             defined by clinical or bronchoscopic evaluation)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Non-survivable burn patients;

          -  history of coagulation disease;

          -  chronic obstructive pulmonary disease(COPD);

          -  pneumonia diagnosed at admission;

          -  inability to confirm definitive diagnosis of inhalation injury and co poisoning or
             Cyanide hydrogen intoxication
